<subSubSection id="C33A651A98595A5BDADCFDA4D118FBF3" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F369198595A5BDADCFDA4D118FBF3" blockId="69.[189,1399,558,1043]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098595A5BDADCFDA4D3C8FDA8" author="Hayman" box="[189,477,558,585]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis id="B954EA8398595A5BDB46FDA4D377FDA8" box="[295,354,558,584]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 68
</bibRefCitation>
, map114) reported 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298595A5BD8DEFDA4D156FDA8" baseAuthorityName="Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[703,835,558,584]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Myopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="whitleyi">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398595A5BD8DEFDA4D156FDA8" box="[703,835,558,584]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">M. whitleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from three localities: Léopoldville (= Kinshasa, Kinshasa City Province), Luluabourg (= Kananga, Kasaï Central Province) and Beno (Mai-Ndombe Province), all in the southwestern part of the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BD8B5FDFED101FD6F" box="[724,788,629,655]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">DRC</collectingCountry>
. Additional specimens were collected in the Kikwit area (Kwilu Province) and in Banana (Kongo Central Province), also in the southwestern part of the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDADCFD30D2E8FD35" box="[189,253,699,725]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">DRC</collectingCountry>
. One further specimen, however, was collected in the northeastern part of the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDEFEFD30D6F5FD35" box="[1183,1248,699,725]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">DRC</collectingCountry>
: 
<quantity id="4CD89B7498595A5BDE8DFD30D722FD35" box="[1260,1335,699,725]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
N of Kasenye (Ituri Province). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098595A5BDB96FD55D0DAFD18" author="Aellen" box="[503,719,734,761]" firstAuthor="Aellen" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref255111" refString="Aellen V. 1952. Contribution a l'etude des chiropteres du Cameroun. Memoire de la Societe neuchateloise de Sciences naturelles 8 (1): 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1952">Aellen (1952: 99)</bibRefCitation>
reported the species from Coquilhatville (= Mbandaka, Equateur Province), but that record could not be traced. The distribution map presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098595A5BDE84FC8AD2E6FCDF" author="Fahr" firstAuthor="Fahr" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" pagination="478 - 479" refId="ref260500" refString="Fahr J. 2013 j. Myopterus whitleyi Bini Winged-mouse Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 478 - 479. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="j">Fahr (2013j: 478)</bibRefCitation>
shows two red areas: one encompassing the southwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BD9C0FCAED1C8FCDF" box="[929,989,805,831]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">DRC</collectingCountry>
records (except for Banana, which is plotted separately) and a second in coastal 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BD883FCC3D12FFC82" box="[738,826,840,866]" name="Nigeria" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
/ 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BD922FCC3D1A8FC82" box="[835,957,840,866]" name="Cameroon" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
(from the mouth of the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDE84FCC3D73DFC82" box="[1253,1320,840,866]" name="Niger" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Niger</collectingCountry>
to the Mount 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDB70FCE0D39EFC65" box="[273,395,875,901]" name="Cameroon" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
area). Furthermore, he plotted single localities in 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BD9A9FCE0D60DFC65" box="[968,1048,875,901]" name="Ghana" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Ghana</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDE2DFCE0D767FC65" box="[1100,1394,875,901]" name="Central African Republic" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Central African Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDADCFC05D31BFC48" box="[189,270,910,936]" name="Gabon" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Gabon</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDB31FC05D3BAFC48" box="[336,431,910,936]" name="Uganda" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Uganda</collectingCountry>
. The SDM map looks very similar, although it doesn’t reach 
<collectingCountry id="F337760198595A5BDEF3FC05D6F7FC48" box="[1170,1250,910,936]" name="Ghana" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Ghana</collectingCountry>
, as we were unable to trace the specific locality for that country. The map also suggests that 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298595A5BDEE3FC38D71DFC2C" baseAuthorityName="Scharff" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1154,1288,946,972]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Myopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="whitleyi">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398595A5BDEE3FC38D71DFC2C" box="[1154,1288,946,972]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">M. whitleyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not occur in the Congolian rainforest, but encircles it both on the north and the south, and the two branches meet again in the Ugandan-Tanzanian border area.
</paragraph>
